<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="356" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,253,1540]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,361,387]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally, the new species differs from other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsholt &amp; Remeikis" authorityYear="2021" box="[1024,1118,363,388]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matrona">
<emphasis box="[1024,1118,363,388]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">matrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group by the golden glossy, grey-brown, apically ornated forewing (
<taxonomicName authority="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1999" box="[699,1146,398,424]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrimaculella">
<emphasis box="[699,894,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">P. nigrimaculella</emphasis>
Puplesis &amp; Robinson
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alleni">
<emphasis box="[1207,1301,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">P. alleni</emphasis>
Puplesis &amp; Robinson
</taxonomicName>
possess a snow-white forewing with very few markings apically). In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis &amp; Karsholt, 2021" authorityName="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis &amp; Karsholt" authorityYear="2021" box="[1273,1396,435,460]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matrona" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1273,1396,435,460]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">P. matrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="15" pageNumber="356" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1999" box="[346,539,470,496]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrimaculella">
<emphasis box="[346,539,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">P. nigrimaculella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the basally very wide and strongly chitinized juxta, and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1999" box="[1269,1360,470,496]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alleni">
<emphasis box="[1269,1360,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">P. alleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the large, triangular lobes of uncus, distally pointed gnathos, and very long juxta (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1095,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,437,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-140@6.[152,1435,417,1913]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 2–3. Diagnostic tool for species identification of the Pseudopostega matrona group and its distribution. 2, pictorial tool for species differentiation; 3, known distribution (map base, courtesy of T. Patterson, USA)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554950" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554950/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,253,1540]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,542,568]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[277,402,542,569]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Figs. 4–16</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 3.8–4.1 mm; wingspan 8.5–8.8 mm (n = 3). Head: palpus cream, short; frontal tuft large, comprised of piliform, snow-white scales (
<figureCitation box="[837,946,578,605]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
); collar very large, distally slightly bilobed (
<figureCitation box="[159,274,614,641]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Figs. 4, 6</figureCitation>
), comprised of lamellar, grey-brown scales with strong golden gloss; scape very large, snow-white, distally with some bronze scales; antenna golden glossy, pale grey-brown, exceeding 2/3 of the forewing. Thorax and tegula grey-brown with strong golden gloss and little purple iridescence. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1230,686,712]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) grey-brown with golden gloss and little purple iridescence in basal half and with white and dark grey-brown markings in apical half (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,758,784]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Apex of forewing curved up, with a large, black apical dot, three brown-black costal strigulae and one brown-black tornal strigula, and a distinctive tuft of dark piliform scales; fringe grey-brown; forewing underside dark grey-brown, without spots or androconia. Hindwing and fringe dark grey-brown with golden gloss and little purple iridescence on upper side and underside. Legs grey-brown with golden gloss and some cream scales, especially abundant on hindleg underside. Abdomen brown with strong golden gloss and little purple iridescence on upper side, pale brown with golden gloss and many white-tipped scales on underside; genital plates golden cream, contrasting with colour of the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[607,744,974,1001]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Figs. 15, 16</figureCitation>
); anal tufts yellowish cream, short (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1228,974,1000]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–16" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,190,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[154,1434,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 4–16. Male adult of Pseudopostega matrona Karsholt &amp; Remeikis sp. nov., holotype (ZMUC). 4–6, details of the head, dorsal view; 7, general view, right side; 8, 9, fragments of hindwing, upper side; 10, head, ventral view; 11, general view; 12, white scales of the forewing; 13, apex of forewing, upper side; 14, abdomen; 15, 16, apex of abdomen ap.d. – apical dot; c. str. – costal strigulae; t. str. – tornal strigula; tft. – tuft of piliform scales" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4554952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4554952/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,253,1540]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,369,1009,1036]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
